Last week, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize failed to appear before Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Health to answer questions regarding the Digital Vibes scandal, saying he was legally advised not to attend the meeting. Chairperson Sibongiseni Dhlomo discusses. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It was a mistake not having Health Minister Zweli Mkhize appear before Parliament. That is the admission of Health Portfolio Committee chair, Sibongiseni Dhlomo. READ: Digital Vibes scandal | Zweli Mkhize apologises He says Mkhize was to meet with them on Thursday, but then he was placed on special leave. Meanwhile, Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly, Lechesa Tsenoli, says it can't drag members before the committee by the collar. Parliament is constitutionally mandated to hold the executive accountable, but did it fail to exercise its oversight role over Health Minister Zweli Mkhize? Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly Lechesa Tsenoli speaks to #eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403 President Cyril Ramaphosa has placed Health Minister Zweli Mhkize on special leave. The Presidency says Mkhize's leave will allow him to attend to the allegations around the Digital Vibes contract. Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will serve as acting Health Minister. Watch the videos above for more details on this story.